  "prompt": "What are stars made out of?",
  "response": "Stars are primarily made out of hydrogen and helium, which together make up about 98% of a star's mass. The rest of a star's mass is composed of heavier elements such as carbon, nitrogen, and oxygen, among others. In the core of a star, hydrogen atoms are fused into helium through nuclear reactions, which release energy in the form of light and heat. This process is what makes stars shine and provides the energy that sustains life on Earth.",
